<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
(Fig. 1). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Erechthias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erechthias minuscula" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula">Erechthias minuscula</taxonomicName>
is probably pantropical in distribution, and occurs widely in South America, the West Indies into southern Florida, USA. 
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson, GS" journalOrPublisher="Monographs on Australian Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" title="Tineid genera of Australia (Lepidoptera)." volume="2" year="1993">Robinson and Nielsen (1993)</bibRefCitation>
also report it from Australia.
